80
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:06,620
Stay here, I'll be right back.

81
00:16:14,003 --> 00:16:16,338
See you later.

82
00:16:18,257 --> 00:16:21,469
It's all right.
She'll be just fine.

83
00:16:21,886 --> 00:16:24,263
Okay, thanks. Bye-bye.

84
00:16:24,597 --> 00:16:26,307
Good morning, teacher.

85
00:16:26,390 --> 00:16:27,725
Hello Sosuke.

86
00:16:27,808 --> 00:16:29,351
How are you?

87
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:36,692
- Sosuke!
- Kumiko...

88
00:16:36,775 --> 00:16:40,029
Like my dress?
Mommy got it for me.

89
00:16:40,112 --> 00:16:41,322
Oh...

90
00:16:41,405 --> 00:16:43,199
Let's play, Sosuke!

91
00:16:43,282 --> 00:16:45,409
Not now. I'm busy.

92
00:16:45,493 --> 00:16:47,036
How come?

93
00:16:47,119 --> 00:16:50,706
- I told you, I'm busy.
- You're no fun.

94
00:16:50,873 --> 00:16:51,916
Yeah!

95
00:17:13,479 --> 00:17:14,939
Ponyo!

96
00:17:22,238 --> 00:17:23,739
Sosuke!

97
00:17:23,906 --> 00:17:24,949
Kumiko...

98
00:17:25,074 --> 00:17:26,575
What's that?

99
00:17:26,742 --> 00:17:28,786
You're not supposed to
bring stuff.

100
00:17:29,161 --> 00:17:33,207
But these trees
aren't on school grounds.

101
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:34,625
Show me.

102
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:37,378
Oh, a goldfish.

103
00:17:37,545 --> 00:17:39,797
It's not a goldfish.
It's Ponyo.

104
00:17:39,922 --> 00:17:42,216
Ponyo? I want to see!

105
00:17:42,466 --> 00:17:44,552
Promise not to tell?

106
00:17:44,635 --> 00:17:45,970
I promise.

107
00:17:48,013 --> 00:17:49,974
Isn't she cute?

108
00:17:56,230 --> 00:18:00,150
It looks fat.
My goldfish is lots cuter.

109
00:18:22,548 --> 00:18:26,927
It's Kumiko's fault.
She was mean to you.

110
00:18:30,598 --> 00:18:32,850
I'll give you
some more water.

111
00:18:54,872 --> 00:18:55,956
Ponyo!

112
00:19:02,963 --> 00:19:03,964
You scared me.

113
00:19:09,261 --> 00:19:14,975
Why, how odd.
That was Sosuke's voice.

114
00:19:15,643 --> 00:19:20,022
But he's supposed
to be in school.

115
00:19:20,189 --> 00:19:22,358
I must be hearing things.

116
00:19:22,524 --> 00:19:24,735
Here I am, Yoshie.

117
00:19:26,195 --> 00:19:30,074
I knew I heard your voice.

118
00:19:31,158 --> 00:19:33,452
Do I have a secret?

119
00:19:33,577 --> 00:19:34,453
Yes!

120
00:19:34,578 --> 00:19:36,121
Bingo!

121
00:19:36,413 --> 00:19:38,999
Okay, what color is my secret?

122
00:19:41,585 --> 00:19:43,504
- Red!
- Red!

123
00:19:43,921 --> 00:19:45,964
Good guess.

124
00:19:46,090 --> 00:19:48,300
How'd you know?

125
00:19:48,425 --> 00:19:49,718
Show us.

126
00:19:49,885 --> 00:19:51,178
All right.

127
00:19:53,764 --> 00:19:55,182
Oh, how pretty!

128
00:19:55,265 --> 00:19:56,934
Very cute!

129
00:19:57,101 --> 00:19:58,310
Her name is Ponyo.

130
00:19:58,435 --> 00:20:01,897
She loves ham
and she can do magic.

131
00:20:02,398 --> 00:20:06,402
I cut my thumb,
but she fixed it.

132
00:20:08,570 --> 00:20:12,199
I wonder if she'd
fix our legs.

133
00:20:12,282 --> 00:20:16,412
We could run around
just like you.

134
00:20:17,079 --> 00:20:20,499
Well, I'd have
to ask Ponyo first.

135
00:20:20,624 --> 00:20:22,835
Can I take a look?

136
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,294
Sure, Toki.

137
00:20:26,130 --> 00:20:28,924
Heavens, it has a face!

138
00:20:30,676 --> 00:20:34,763
Put it back
before it brings a tsunami!

139
00:20:34,847 --> 00:20:37,558
You're so superstitious, Toki.

140
00:20:38,016 --> 00:20:41,478
That's what
the old stories say.

141
00:20:41,603 --> 00:20:43,564
Fish like that are bad luck.

142
00:20:46,108 --> 00:20:49,486
The tsunami! It's here!

143
